 Abstract: 
 Recursive Energy Intelligence for Precision Laser Healing 
 &nbsp; 
 This work introduces a new way to improve how focused lasers are used to treat cancer. Todays laser treatments can be powerful, but they sometimes go too far or not far enough. They might miss part of the tumor or harm healthy tissue because they don&acirc;&euro;&trade;t adjust in real time. 
 &nbsp; 
 The method presented here creates a smarter system. It listens to the body during treatment, adjusting itself continuously. It knows how much energy has been used, how much has been lost, and how much is still needed. It watches how the tissue reacts and makes changes instantly to stay safe and effective. 
 &nbsp; 
 Instead of firing energy in one fixed pattern, this system sends energy in steps that respond to what's happening. It balances how much is given and how much is needed, keeping the process from running out of control. It also remembers what happened in earlier steps to improve what it does next. 
 &nbsp; 
 This approach leads to more accurate treatments, fewer side effects, and better results. It works like a learning system that treats each patient in a personal way. By thinking in cycles growth, correction, and balance it creates a new path forward for medical tools that learn as they work. 
 &nbsp; 
 In short, this is a healing system that adapts, protects, and evolves as it treats making cancer care smarter, safer, and more precise.

